TOTAL: 72 Cards   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">With Delia I first play a vellup and get another vellup.  I play that vellup and get a elder vellup.  I play the elder vellup and get any creature I need. I then use recurring dreams if I need to and play anything else I have. She usually lives until I beet my opponent&#39;s first magi.<br>
<br>
When Defender of the Sky comes into play, I first play xyx elder, xyx minor, and xyx along with any other xyx.  I use gathering clouds on xyx minor and use shockstorm if my opponents have creatures out.  I try to keep only xyx out if I can and keep powering up xyx elder, so I can keep using shockstorm.<br>
<br>
Whith Shimmer I get all of her starting cards and storm shield.  I play pharan, cloud narth, storm shield, and ant other creatures.  I then use healing storm on any one of my creatures and shooting star if I have enough energy. A strategy for Shimmer is to get rid of all her energy for creature bond and strengthen on storm shield.<br>
